I've gotten a nvidia 760 from some family members that they just had in a bag. I'm not sure it is working, but will try to play around with it.

Could you see if adding `-nomovies` to the launch options changes anything? If you have anything that uses `%command%` then put it after e.g. `PROTON_LOG=1 %command% -nomovies`. Or just on it's own.

@atif-rehman-ideofuzion one more thing you can try is disabling vaapi when starting the game:

LIBVA_DRIVER_NAME="" %command%

So far I know only of AMD GPU cases where it helped, but it shouldn't hurt to try it.

@Drek282 2 more requests to attempt to get to the bottom of this in case it is in our power to fix: 
1) Could you "verify the integrity of the files" for Proton 6.3-4 (under properties -> local files) - just to make sure something didn't get messed up in there.
2) Could you get a log with +module,+dinput added to the rest of the channels?
